//www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slackershaman</span><br>  Posts: 328<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 2:04:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> I posted this in another thread where it probably won't seen as well, so I'll try here through the magic of cut and paste:<br>
<br>
I'd say there is one single thing that needs to be addressed on any calender or scheduling revision.<br>
<br>
<br>
If something goes wrong, if a reservation is not abided by, if someone steals your spawn, What should be done about it?<br>
<br>
<br>
I haven't seen an answer to that question that works. Since there is an active sentiment that is pro-FCFS, FFA, XFL, and WWF in many powerful guilds out there how are you going to police when something goes wrong?<br>
<br>
Seeing as there is a lack of an administrative option until then, is it worthwhile to have a reservation system that cannot have authority to police itself? If you do make an penalty, what says they have to take/accept it?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthomus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thomus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>dabomb</span><br>  Posts: 821<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 8:47:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> Hiya Ulver! /waves<br>
<br>
Just wanted to say hello bro! hehe<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usyrillian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syrillian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 76<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 8:57:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> See, that is the paper tiger of the boards yet it is the people that make up the server and their general concern for others that has kept the system respected.  Nothing more.  <br>
<br>
-Syrillian <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujasiofneriak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jasi of Neriak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/23/01 11:45:49 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ang.mux.net/smjasi.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> I once told someone in the game that the only real thing of value you have in EQ is your reputation. While there's alot of room for stupidity, once you've ruined your rep, it's a long, arduous road to repair it.<br>
<br>
Yes, the reservation/board system is essentially one of honor, but there is a great deal of power behind the majority of the server and guilds agreeing to abide by these guidelines. <br>
<br>
So, in essence, the moderaters of this board may not have the authority to punish people who don't follow the reservation system (other than probably preventing them from signing up legitimately for anything again), but we as a server and collection of guilds CAN stand up and uphold this system. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>GD RPers</span><br>  Posts: 2040<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/24/01 2:18:41 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soj/itsme.jpg height=153 width=142></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> Great point, that's a fundamental flaw built in to calendars.<br>
<br>
Calendars need support of EVERYONE, including and especially people at the top, to work.<br>
<br>
The 3 most powerful guilds on the server have serious issues with the calendar, feel it's fundamentally flawed and do not want to see an already flawed calendar expand.<br>
<br>
If 1 of the guild doesn't respect an aspect of the calendar, there is NO recourse, if you remove them from being able to use the calendar they'll just ffa and have their fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unadiabrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nadia brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 210<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/24/01 4:16:44 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~karl23/_images/nadia.jpg width=99 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> I have yet to see an upper level guild that doesnt care about their reputation.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ulver>Ulver</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slackershaman</span><br>  Posts: 331<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/24/01 7:40:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> DISCLAIMER: I read the boards occasionally. I don't know the facts here. I know my vague perceptions.<br>
<br>
Reputation is something that only goes so far it seems. People say that the FG system didn't work. The spawns were taken. Ragefire was killed. Problems were encountered. People came out and rose a cry against it.<br>
<br>
In most cases it seems like people were unsatisfied and from what I can tell, people were repeat offenders. This seems to be a pretty clear example that the &quot;reputation&quot; method of police isn't working.<br>
<br>
I'd love to hear otherwise.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukestrithebard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KestriTheBard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 242<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/24/01 8:03:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> Ulver,<br>
<br>
In my opinion (read - I don't speak for my guild on any matter), reputation is the only thing that we can use here.  And you are right in that one bad apple will ruin the bushel.  This needs to be something that everyone has to work together on, unfortunately.  <br>
<br>
To me Brell has built and incredible community and is very good at working out problems (and dealing with problem children) within these boards.  For every single problem that we have had we have had 100-150 raids that had no problem.  <br>
<br>
As Veranon said there are really enough mobs to go around, just the epics and such have caused a bottleneck (I personally never see myself getting mine do to the new Trak guts spawn and the scales being so hard to get and wanted by a lot of people now).  <br>
<br>
I have fought in many places and have never seen our guild flamed for taking a special spawn (at least since I have been in it) or hogging something, or even stepping on people's toes.  Why is that?  We supported the reservation system (sometimes to a fault) and we had respect for the other people on our server.  If there ever was an issue we were able to work it out amiably with others. <br>
<br>
Does that mean we are less greedy than other guilds? Maybe... Does that mean we have better PR people?  Hell no! You ever read some of Kruunch's posts?  All it means is that by some lucky chance, or choice we have made we have been able to uphold the spirit that has been created on this board and in the reservation system. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uconanb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>conanb</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 168<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 10:42:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> id say just do away with all of the reservations.  scheduling a  time to kill a dragon  is kinda like scheduling a businesss meeting or scheduling a plane flight. wheres the adventure in that? wheres the spontenaity?<br>
<br>
now of course not having reservations dont mean that you  dont have respect for other people. i would never propose that we all train each other as  we all try to down  trak, or any stupidity like that.  fcfs with decent respect for your fellow game players.<br>
<br>
thats how it is in velious and from what i seen it works great there.<br>
<br>
disclaimer---these are my own views and not those of loh.  i just happen to be a guy who likes more spontenaity.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urelbeekeinre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Relbeek Einre</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>uncommonly Good</span><br>  Posts: 2649<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 11:45:00 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.tigerden.com/~twilight/keebler-60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> Seems like a case of divide and conquer to me.<br>
<br>
Sow mistrust and dissention among the rabble to wear away at the unified front and concern for reputation that is preventing certain uberguilds from going fully FFA. A poke here, a jab here, confusion over timezones there, &quot;oops&quot; here, enough to make some people rail against the &quot;accidental&quot; repeated toe-stepping but for others to wish to grant the offenders the benefit of the doubt. Get the two groups fighting amongst themselves, and the formerly unified groups of people defending the calendar system can no longer do it. FFA happens, and the conniving guilds who deliberately worked for it have clean hands. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ulver>Ulver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slackershaman</span><br>  Posts: 332<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 12:20:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> If FFA happens and if it is decided that it is not where the server wants to be, whats to be done about it? Although an interesting statement Relbeek, whats the consquences of the actions? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urelbeekeinre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Relbeek Einre</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>uncommonly Good</span><br>  Posts: 2653<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 2:21:59 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.tigerden.com/~twilight/keebler-60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> One's most valuable asset is one's reputation. Or so they say.<br>
<br>
There is no guild on Brell so independent and powerful that it lives in a vacuum, separate from the rest of us.<br>
<br>
The consequences of social exclusion and ostracization, coupled with the promise of those consequences being lifted by getting with the program, are effective tools if we still have the resolve to implement them properly.<br>
<br>
Let's say for the sake of an argument that Silent Redemption decided to screw the reservation system and go FFA. Ulver Stonemace is a member of SR. Ulver Stonemace is friends in the real world with a bunch of the members of Shields of Light and online friends with a lot of people. Those people look at Silent Redemption and say &quot;No love for you&quot; - and actively exclude anyone wearing the guildtag, including Ulver Stonemace. In the real world, Ulver's friends wonder at him why he continues to be part of a guild that seems so interested in tearing apart what we of Brell spent two years putting together. What would Ulver do? What would every other member of Silent Redemption do when faced with similar treatment? <br>
<br>
The power of ostracization is remarkable if you can get enough people with the program. Many religions institutionalized the practice when sect members 'strayed from the flock.' Many, like the Mormons, Jehovah's Witnesses, and Scientologists, still use the practice. It's been called shunning, excommunication, disfellowshipping, disconnection. And it's remarkably effective when used right.<br>
<br>
Or we can just roll over and take it in the ass.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzestrenocya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zestrenocya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Norrath's Finest Taxi Service [Mod]</span><br>  Posts: 1233<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 5:29:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> Reeblek:<br>
<br>
I have about 10 RL friends on Brell.  They were RL friends before EQ.  They'll be RL friends after EQ.  Nothing that goes on in this game has any bearing on my real life.  I would be so bold as to say that it has no bearing on theirs either.<br>
<br>
None of those RL friends, btw, are in Silent Redemption.  They're all above level 50 with one exception. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urelbeekeinre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Relbeek Einre</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>uncommonly Good</span><br>  Posts: 2657<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 7:04:01 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.tigerden.com/~twilight/keebler-60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> If I ninjalooted, scammed, KSed, trained, or tried to wreck other people's fun on EQ, I feel confident that would reflect on my trustworthiness in the real world too.<br>
<br>
I don't see the logic in saying 'what I do on EQ doesn't count'. If you're playing baseball and are caught throwing spitballs, you can't say &quot;That was just me playing baseball, it doesn't reflect on me in the real world.&quot; Because EQ is a game that requires a computer instead of leather mitts and bats, doesn't make one's lousy actions somehow less relevant.<br>
<br>
Regardless, in-game pressure can be pretty intense. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utrylliumcalaquendi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tryllium Calaquendi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 8:30:05 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eatel.net/~usafcajun/drunks/sigpics/sigpictryllium.gif width=80 height=80></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> Being rather low level (Tryllium is only 45 now and she's my main), I have not played with any of SR's folks (except Nimue's alt enchanter who was not SR guilded).  However, I have heard nothing but good things about them as a guild and as individuals in-game.  Yet I have trouble reconciling Nillon's statements on this board with the attitude and viewpoint I associate with SR.<br>
<br>
Nillon, I just wonder if you are speaking only for yourself when you post, or if a lot of SR folks feel as you do but have a &quot;nicer&quot; public persona in-game...  you seem almost angry and sort of chip-on-the-shoulder-like... am I just being naive?  I don't know... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzestrenocya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zestrenocya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Norrath's Finest Taxi Service [Mod]</span><br>  Posts: 1235<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 10:30:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> Reeb:<br>
<br>
That's probably true.  However, I don't ninja, KS, train, etc.....However, I still debate the value of linking RL to a game.  Certainly one's in game persona is linked to one's real life persona.  I wouldn't presume to debate that at all.  But just because I have RL friends who play EQ doesn't mean we get together and talk about how uber SR is or how uber their guild is or what we should conspire to get each other in game.  Usually, we talk about something other than EQ.  Naturally, since so many of us play the game, the subject comes up from time to time, but I don't think I've ever gotten together with one of my friends and said, &quot;hey...I know...let's talk about EQ!&quot;<br>
<br>
We spend enough of our free time doing stuff like that.  Its nice to be able to hang out with friends and play the Great Dalmuti or something where EQ's not a part of things. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubrenstakdagrump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brenstak Dagrump</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pervert</span><br>  Posts: 1132<br> <font color=#CC9900>(4/25/01 11:11:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Biggest Concern</span><hr size=1> Tryllium -<br>
<br>
Alot of Nillon's statements on this board are reaction statements without a lot of thought put into them.  If you read some old off-topic stuff (assuming it is still there) you will see a little more of what Nillon is about.<br>
<br>
